text: "What physiological change causes the oxygen-hemoglobin dissociation curve to shift to the left?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Increased temperature", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "Increased 2,3-BPG", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Decreased pH", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Decreased CO\u2082", "is_correct": true}],
explanation: "A **left shift of the oxyhemoglobin dissociation curve** occurs with **decreased CO\u2082**, reflecting reduced hydrogen ion concentration (alkalosis).<br><br>This increases hemoglobin\u2019s **affinity for oxygen**, favoring oxygen loading in the lungs. In contrast, increased temperature, increased 2,3-BPG, and decreased pH cause a **right shift**.",
