tags: ["ZVRecommended", "PYQ", "INI-CET May 2024"],
text: "A 40-year-old male presented to OPD with complaints of excessive daytime sleepiness, and his wife also complains that he snores a lot at night during sleep. Which of the following is incorrect regarding his condition?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Increased tone of the pharyngeal muscles worsens obstruction", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "B", "text": "Fall of oxygen saturation triggers waking episodes at night", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Episodes of apnea increase stress on the heart", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Hypoxemia stimulates respiratory effort", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "Clues:<br><br>* **Excessive daytime sleepiness**\n* **Loud snoring**<br><br>Classic for **Obstructive Sleep Apnea (OSA)**<br><br>Sleep\n\u00a0\u00a0 \u2193\n\u2193 Pharyngeal muscle tone\n\u00a0\u00a0 \u2193\nAirway collapse\n\u00a0\u00a0 \u2193\nApnea (no airflow)\n\u00a0\u00a0 \u2193\n\u2193 Oxygen saturation\n\u00a0\u00a0 \u2193\nArousal from sleep\n\u00a0\u00a0 \u2193\nCycle repeats<br><br>| **Feature** | **OSA Mechanism** |\n| ------- | ------------- |\n| Muscle tone | \u2193 (causes obstruction) |\n| Oxygen level | \u2193 (hypoxemia) |\n| Arousal | Triggered by hypoxia |\n| Cardiac effect | \u2191 Stress (HTN, arrhythmia) |\n| Respiratory drive | \u2191 due to hypoxemia |<br><br>\u00a0**OSA Risk Factors**<br><br>| **Factor** | **Effect** |\n| ------ | ------ |\n| Obesity | \u2191 airway narrowing |\n| Large neck circumference | \u2191 obstruction |\n| Alcohol | \u2193 muscle tone |\n| Sedatives | \u2193 muscle tone |<br><br>| **Treatment** | **Role** |\n| --------- | ---- |\n| **CPAP** | First-line |\n| Weight loss | Essential |\n| Surgery | Selected cases |",
