text: "A 14-year-old boy is brought to the emergency department for follow-up after experiencing a near-drowning incident that led to ARDS. He was mechanically ventilated for 2 weeks and subsequently discharged. The patient now reports persistent exertional dyspnea and mild fatigue. Which of the following parameters is most likely increased compared to a child with normal cardiopulmonary function?",
