explanation: "Acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS) causes diffuse alveolar damage and thickening of the alveolar\u2013capillary membrane, impairing gas exchange.<br><br>* Impaired oxygen diffusion and V/Q mismatch\n* Leads to an increased alveolar\u2013arterial (A\u2013a) oxygen gradient<br><br>\nOther expected findings after ARDS:<br><br>* Reduced diffusion capacity (DLCO)\n* Restrictive lung pattern on pulmonary function tests<br><br>\nImportant point:<br><br>An increased A\u2013a gradient indicates impaired oxygen transfer from alveoli to blood, seen in conditions like ARDS, pneumonia, pulmonary fibrosis, and V/Q mismatch.",
